Baseline Scenario (Most Probable)
Scenario 3 (28.86% Rupture Probability) is identified as the most realistic baseline for the Monday opening price:
Balanced calibration of geopolitical risk and market resilience
Maintains full global buffer capacity ($60.00)
Projects a moderate upside gap consistent with typical geopolitical risk pricing in crude oil markets
Avoids overly conservative (Scenario 1) or extreme black-swan (Scenario 5) bias
Key Notes
Trading Hours (Beijing Time, DST): Monday 06:00 – Saturday 04:45
Drivers: Middle East geopolitical tensions, supply disruption risks, and global energy buffer dynamics
